annotation.TEXT: Okay, I've gotta be really careful here, because there's a whole lot of bottomless pit below me.
BGM: CUSTOM - Cave Music 2: Dark Cave
MOOOONNN!!!!! Aw, but I missed the really big score...
So, the portmanteau of "Dark" and "Cave" it is!

Hey, thanks Mr. Disco! Now I've got my peach back again! Now, I could backtrack to check out that wall where the partial coin arrow was, but... nah. Maybe I'll check it out at a later time, if I remember.
Peach power acquired! Now for Darkave again...
I hope there aren't any concealed bottomless pits, but I guess I could use my fireballs to scout ahead.
...What? I've unlocked two levels at once here! I wasn't expecting that!
Seriously, stop playing sloppily.
You can stop watching now if you want. There are no more annotations past this point.
How much more is there to this level? I don't have much time left.
Yeah, I've gotta be more cautious now with those Blarggoshis around.
Umm... I don't feel like backtracking to find out. Yeah, nuts to that.
Ooh, I see the silhouette of a springboard!
Ac yn awr, gÃªm bonws cyflymder chwerthinllyd!
Whoa, I almost got a pencil up my butt back there.
There's a bat that's not trying to masquerade as a Yoshi.
Okay, no more disco for you.
Ha! He missed the shell! I want to see that again!
Please take me straight to the goal!
BGM: CUSTOM - Super Mario World - Athletic (Remix)
That unlocks Running Cave. But, I'm not going there yet. Instead, I want to get a peach somewhere and then check out what's beyond the wall at the beginning of Darkave.
Well, I got 30, which I guess isn't terrible.
Thank you!
Hmm... You'd think there might be something hidden above vertical lines of coins like these...
Yeah, I took a screenshot of that back on April 1st. Hello, and welcome back to Something else! Alright, there's only one place to go now... Yoshi's Mountain! So, let's-a-go!
Green shell = Darkave. Yellow shell = Kill Banzai Bill. May the better shell win.

ARGH!!! Sorry about this, guys, but I'm not reuploading this file now (I wish I'd noticed this issue before I uploaded this to YouTube and did about 9 minutes worth of annotating...). However, I will reupload this slowed-down footage at its proper speed as an "and a half" episode next time! For now, I guess you'll get a slowed-down sneak peek of the entrance to this level's secret area...
GAAAMMMEEE!!! I knew I should've left before that could have a chance to happen...
Goal tape average so far: 1066 / 31 = 34.387 stars each.
Ha! Got it! Now, can I get anything decent as far as bonus stars go? (I kind of wish I didn't take that flower at the start. The peach would've been far better for this level.)
Goal tape average so far: 1036 / 30 = 34.533 stars each.
Uh, oh. That's most definitely a pit. Hopefully all such pits will be easily identifiable.
So, was that koopa supposed to miss the shell like that, or was he intended to go disco?
These jumps are definitely getting trickier...
At least I can't accidentally break these blocks with spin jumps!
Ooh, flying 1-up! Oh, there's the goal! But wait, I'm pretty sure I can get that 1-up...
Okay, now this definitely qualifies as a dark cave (or a dark avenue, or an average amount of darkness).
Whoa! Now Blarggs are masquerading as Yoshis! (And they've somehow adapted to be able to survive outside of lava!)
Looks like there are some giant dark bubbles floating around here. I'd better pay close attention for them.
Oh, nice. At least I get a replacement peach here. Hmm... I wonder what I missed out on to the left...
Huh, were those coins supposed to be an emoticon or something?
To be continued...
Ooh, nice shot, blue duder!
Whoa! Missed the ledge I was aiming for. Good thing there was stuff below for me to land on!
Huh, that almost looked like part of a coin arrow against that wall there. However, I don't have my peach anymore, so if there is something hidden way up there, I'm not getting it now.
Moon count: 6 1-ups earned this time: 7.22. Bonus game average so far: 68.91 / 9 = 7.65667 1-ups each.
Whoa, careful with scrolling the screen backwards, because that can cause bubbles to respawn behind me.
Don't jump too high here, obviously.
Hi, Yoshis! ...Wait, those aren't Yoshis! They're just koopas hopelessly masquerading as Yoshis!

Umm... What? It's not supposed to be in slow motion now. Uhh, WMM? Did you screw up my footage again? I don't know why WMM sometimes glitches like this when it comes to the "speed up" and "slow down" effects, honestly...
Also, not letting myself get smacked by that koopyoshduder would've helped too...
Zwee! I've become embiggened again!

Hmm... Do I want the flower? Well, there may or may not be something of interest beyond this wall to the right, but I think I'll wait until a revisit to check that out (just so I can Start+Select if there's nothing but pit over there). So, yeah. I'll take the flower now.

And, I just double-checked my WMM project file for this movie, it is actually running at normal speed here like it should be, but apparently, it decided to erroneously put the "slow down" effect on this part of the movie when I saved the movie file (the part where I collected the peach was meant to be slowed, but it should've returned to normal speed when I returned to the overworld).
Oh, hey. It's a peach that I don't need right now.
Also, not letting myself get smacked by a bat would've helped...
Well, I guess that koopa never needed to go disco...
Wow, how did I not get hit right there? (+1 graze)
And the green shell is victorious this time!
Huh. This doesn't seem like a dark cave...
So... There's Kill Banzai Bill, and... Darkave. Well, there's only one way for me to decide which way to go! You guys should know what's next!
BGM: Super Mario Kart - Character Select

R! R! R! MORE POWER!!!
